💡 Query:

INSERT INTO Students (id, name, age)
VALUES 
(2, 'Priya', 21),
(3, 'Amit', 22);


| Term                 | Meaning        | What it Does                                  |
| -------------------- | -------------- | --------------------------------------------- |
| **INSERT**           | Add new data   | Tells SQL to insert (add) new rows            |
| **INTO**             | Target table   | Says *which table* to insert into             |
| **Students**         | Table name     | The table where data will be stored           |
| **(id, name, age)**  | Column list    | Columns that will receive the values          |
| **VALUES**           | Data to insert | Introduces actual values to add               |
| **(2, 'Priya', 21)** | Row 1 data     | Adds a row with id=2, name=Priya, age=21      |
| **(3, 'Amit', 22)**  | Row 2 data     | Adds another row with id=3, name=Amit, age=22 |

🧩 1️⃣ CREATE TABLE — Make a new table

Creates a structure to store data.

CREATE TABLE Students (
  id INT,
  name VARCHAR(50),
  age INT
);


🧩 2️⃣ INSERT INTO — Add new data

Adds new rows (records) into a table.

INSERT INTO Students (id, name, age)
VALUES 
(1, 'Rahul', 20),
(2, 'Priya', 21);


//🧩 3️⃣ SELECT — View data

Fetch or read data from the table.

SELECT * FROM Students;


🧩 4️⃣ WHERE — Filter data

Show only rows that match a condition.

SELECT * FROM Students WHERE age > 20;


🧩 5️⃣ UPDATE — Change existing data

Modify the data of existing rows.

UPDATE Students
SET age = 22
WHERE name = 'Priya';

🧠 Changes Priya’s age to 22.


6️⃣ DELETE — Remove data

Delete specific rows from the table.

DELETE FROM Students WHERE id = 1;


🧠 Deletes the student whose ID is 1.


🧩 7️⃣ ALTER TABLE — Change table structure

Add or remove columns in an existing table.

ALTER TABLE Students ADD email VARCHAR(50);


🧠 Adds a new column called email.

🧩 8️⃣ ORDER BY — Sort data

Arrange rows in ascending or descending order.

SELECT * FROM Students ORDER BY age DESC;


🧠 Shows students from oldest to youngest.

🧩 9️⃣ DROP TABLE — Delete the whole table

Removes the table and all its data.

DROP TABLE Students;


🧠 Deletes the table completely from the database.




